div.p:
Againe, We muſt watch for the day of Judgment;
                  Judgment.


as Death leaves us, ſo Judgment will find us: Therefore we ſhould conſider with our ſelves ſeriouſly, the ſtrictneſſe of the account we are to give at the dreadful day of the Son of man, when all works ſhall be brought to a Touch-ſtone, and all ſecrets ſhall be Preached on the Houſe top. It is an excellent thing, when a man doth conſider theſe things before hand; when a man hath looked upon his thoughts, for they ſhall be Judged; and upon his ſpeeches, and upon all his wayes, for they ſhall all be brought before the Judgment Seat of God; and according as a man hath done, ſuch reward he ſhall receive for evermore.
